## How to Know When It's Time for a Redesign

If you're wondering whether it's time to update your site, here are 5 signs your business needs a new website. These are issues we see all the time across South Wales — and they often hold companies back from reaching more customers.

At [NC Digital](/), we help local businesses create modern, fast, mobile-ready websites that actually generate leads. If the points below sound familiar, you might be due for a rebuild.

> "If your website hasn't had a proper update in 3+ years, it's likely underperforming — no matter how nice it looked when it launched."
> NC Digital

#### 1. Your Website Looks Outdated

If your site still looks like it's from 2016, people will notice — and not in a good way. Design trends change fast, and a modern layout helps build instant trust.

#### 2. It's Not Mobile-Friendly

Over half your traffic is coming from phones. If your site doesn't work well on mobile, users bounce — and Google won't rank it as high in search results.

#### 3. Slow Load Times

If your homepage takes 5+ seconds to load, that's a problem. A slow website loses customers before you've even said hello. It also affects your rankings.

#### 4. You're Not Showing Up on Google

If you're not ranking for your own business name or key local services, your site may not be set up correctly for SEO. A rebuild can fix this at the core.

#### 5. It's Hard to Update or Add Content

Still relying on someone else to change basic text or images? You shouldn't have to. A new site on WordPress gives you easy control without needing to code.

## Why These Website Issues Hurt Your Business

A website is more than just a digital brochure — it's your sales rep, lead generator, and credibility builder. If it's underperforming, you are too.

